1.title: Gooble
1.plot: Yo Gabba Gabba! stars host DJ Lance Rock who brings to life four friendly monsters and a robot in a colorful land of music and laughter. The series highlights simple life lessons for preschoolers, through song and animation.

2.title: DJ Lance's Super Music & Toy Room
2.plot: DJ Lance loses the magic star on his hat, so he brings the Gabba friends to his music room to help him search. Guests: Mark Mothersbaugh, Bootsy Collins, Erykah Badu, Biz Markie, Questlove, Jack McBrayer, Paul Scheer, Kemba Russell, Leslie Hall ,Papas Fritas

3.title: A Very Awesome Christmas
3.plot: Santa visits Gabbaland with guests: Tori Spelling, Tony Hawk, Mark Mothersbaugh, Leslie Hall, Cults, My Chemical Romance

4.title: Show
4.plot: DJ Lance and friends go to the Super Music Friends Show to watch music videos from other episodes and visit the Swami.

5.title: Mermaids
5.plot: Foofa and Toodee become mermaids and go on an underwater adventure with Tammy the Mermaid.

6.title: Olympics
6.plot: When the Gabba Land gang learns about the Olympics, they decide to compete in their own games to win medals and have a good time at the Yo Gabba-lympics!

7.title: Shopping
7.plot: The Gabba friends learn about food, spills, and grocery shopping.

8.title: Super Spies
8.plot: Jason Bateman guests as the bad spy who steals all the balloons from the Gabbaland balloon art party. Guests: Jason Bateman, Biz Markie, Peter Bjorn & John

9.title: Dinosaur
9.plot: The friendly monsters of yo gabba gabba land make friends with some awesome dinosaurs.

10.title: Restaurant
10.plot: The Gabba friends take a ride to a restaurant and learn how to order and behave.

11.title: Quest
11.plot: : The Gabba friends travel to a medieval village to help a miniature king restore order in his kingdom by befriending a pesky dragon bully.

12.title: Farm
12.plot: DJ Lance and his Gabba Land friends visit a farm where Farmer Josh teaches them about farm animals, growing vegetables, living on a farm, and even holding a Farmers' Market. Plus, a good old-fashioned farmyard hoedown!

13.title: Day Camp
13.plot: The Gabba friends and siblings learn new games and crafts at Day Camp.

16.title: Gabba Revue
16.plot: The Gabbas put on a music show.

1.title: Eat
1.plot: The characters learn the fun of eating vegetables and healthy meals; from "Party in my Tummy" and "Snacky Snack Snack" where the vegetables plead to participate, to "Try it you'll Like it."Guest Stars: Elijah Wood

2.title: Summer
2.plot: All the characters in Gabba Land use the outdoors and friends to capture the happiness of summertime. Guest Stars: The Aquabats

3.title: Fun
3.plot: All the Gabba characters learn different ways to have fun. Eating your breakfast is a great way. The characters learn to eat the healthy portions: eggs and fruit. Guest Stars: The Aggrolites and Roy Ellis

4.title: Dance
4.plot: The music and the activities in the Dance episode are specific to participating with the Gabba characters throughout the entire show. Guest Star: Hector Jiminez "Jumping Jellyfish song"

5.title: Sleep
5.plot: In this episode all the characters learn to use different ideas and the benefits of napping and sleeping.Guest Star: Smoosh

6.title: Happy
6.plot: The Happy episode doesn't shy away from losing a game or being sad, but teaches the characters how to overcome moment of feeling sad.Guest Stars: The Salteens

7.title: Friends
7.plot: In this episode the characters learn how friends play a large part in the way we feel about others and themselves. Songs teach the characters who their friends are and how to have fun with them.Guest Star: Mya

8.title: Careful
8.plot: This episode is the characters learn to be safe in all they do, like in the "Danger" and "Up and Down" songs, but just as important, learn how to pick themselves up and try it again in "Shake it Off." Guest Stars: Supernova

9.title: Scary
9.plot: The upbeat music and befriending animations bring an endearing quality to the many things the characters don't like, including foods. Guest Star: Leslie Hall "Razzle Dazzle"

10.title: Halloween
10.plot: It's time for the characters to dress up in outrageous costumes and take part in gathering their own private stash of candy. Guest Stars: Shiny Toy Guns

11.title: Greetings
11.plot: The characters learn how to greet different people, while bringing fun new ways to introduce yourself. Guest Star: Nikki Flore, "Twirly Whirly"

12.title: Move
12.plot: This isn't about moving locations it's about locomotion and all the different ways to enjoy movement. Guest Star: Tony Hawk

13.title: Together
13.plot: Many times discovery is done individually, but in this episode the characters learn to enjoy discovery with another person. Guest Stars: The Wolfgramms

14.title: Christmas
14.plot: So much of Christmas is wrapped up in what we receive, but this episode is more about giving. The characters learn to embody the generous spirit of the season, making it fun to give. Guest Star: Snow Princess Claymation

15.title: Car
15.plot: It's time for the characters to going for a ride in a car. The characters are taught about safety and traveling.Guest Stars: Sugarland "Electric Eel"

16.title: Share
16.plot: In this episode the characters have no concept of what is theirs or how to share even if it's not theirs to play with.Guest Stars: Cornelius

17.title: Find
17.plot: Imagination leads to discovery as the characters uncover many things that may be different or frightening. Guest Stars: Sean Kingston "Mini Spinny"

18.title: Train
18.plot: Not only does Train focus on the joy of riding on trains, but it also shows the characters that it's okay to be scared. Guest Stars: Laila Ali "The Dog"

19.title: Love
19.plot: We know that our parents, friends and family love us but what about the other things that surround us? Guest Stars: The Postmarks

20.title: Imagine
20.plot: The best part of discovery is using your imagination, and in this episode discovering their imagination opens the world. Guest Stars: The Shins

1.title: Teeth
1.plot: Muno has a loose tooth and wiggles it until it comes out. Muno writes a note about his tooth and the Tooth Fairy brings him a toothbrush.Guest Stars: Amy Sedaris, Datarock

2.title: Birthday
2.plot: It's Brobee's birthday and the gang gets birthday presents for him. But Brobee gets sad because he thinks everyone has forgotten about his birthday.Guest Stars: Melora Hardin, The Ting Tings

3.title: Games
3.plot: Everyone loves to play games with friends. The Gabba gang plays a slew of games including Hide and Seek, Peek-a-Boo, Simon Says, Red Light, Green Light and more. Guest Stars: Mates of State

4.title: Green
4.plot: The Gabba gang learns to care for their environment by watering plants, not littering, cleaning up the trash and recycling. Guest Stars: Sal Masakela, Ethan Bortnick

5.title: Talent
5.plot: The Gabba gang learns that everyone has different talents and that practices makes perfect. Everyone uses their special talent to make something. Guest Stars: Amare Stoudemire, Hot Hot Heat

6.title: Space
6.plot: The Gabba gang goes on a space adventure in a flying saucer. They look through a telescope at the stars and planets. In space they meet new friends and discover a new planet.Guest Stars: Electrocutie

7.title: Weather
7.plot: The Gabba gang experience different weather conditions. They sing in the rain, play in the snow, get blown around in the wind and are happy when the sun comes out. Guest Stars: Jack McBrayer, Paul Scheer, Paul Williams

8.title: Robot
8.plot: The Gabba gang learns about machines and Plex sings about being a robot. They learn about electricity and energy.Guest Stars: ASIMO, Rhys Darby, Money Mark

9.title: Differences
9.plot: The Gabba gang learns that it's okay to be different and they point out the differences in each other like color, size, etc.Guest Stars: I'm From Barcelona

10.title: Animals
10.plot: Foofa loves animals and she tracks an animal to find out about it. The Gabba gang also discovers some silly animals that could only be found in Gabbaland. Guest Stars: Jimmy Eat World

11.title: Band
11.plot: The characters are interested in learning to play music and decide to start a band. Guest Stars: Lady Tigra, New Gabba Band

12.title: Big
12.plot: Brobee gets frustrated about being the little one and wants to know what it's like to be big like DJ Lance. He accidentally switches places with DJ Lance and grows big!Guest Star: Jem

13.title: Mystery
13.plot: Toodee and Plex go searching for Foofa who has disappeared. Toodee finds clues to solve the mystery.

14.title: Family
14.plot: Muno's whole family comes to visit and the Gabba gang learns about their family tree. DJ Lance reflects on when all the characters were babies and his sister Kemba makes an appearance. Guest Stars: The Roots

15.title: Ride
15.plot: The gang enjoy the outdoors, including surfing, skateboarding, go-carting and biking.

16.title: Boat
16.plot: The Gabba gang discovers a box with Viking costumes and a map. After dressing up in their costumes, they go on a boat ride adventure discovering a new land and new friends.

17.title: New Friends
17.plot: Jack Black arrives in Gabbaland riding a mini dirt bike. He's lost and scared, but soon makes friends with the Gabba gang and they help him find his way back home. Featured songs include: "Don't Get Lost," "Friend Song" and "Goodbye Song."

18.title: Art
18.plot: The Gabba gang mix paint colors to get new shades and paint a picture. Everyone makes a piece of art and they have an art show.

19.title: Dress Up
19.plot: The Gabba gang likes to dress up and play pretend. DJ Lance gives them a costume box and they pull out shoes, put on silly hats and dress up as cowboys.

20.title: Clean
20.plot: The Gabba gang learns the importance of cleaning up.

1.title: School
1.plot: Brobee and Toodee discover there is no reason to be afraid of going to school. Miss Angela teaches them fun things and they have Show and Tell.

2.title: Adventure
2.plot: Muno and friends go on an Indiana Jones like adventure! They travel through a jungle under Gabbaland and find the golden treasure.

3.title: Nature
3.plot: Yo Gabba Gabba! stars host DJ Lance Rock who brings to life four friendly monsters and a robot in a colorful land of music and laughter. The series highlights simple life lessons for preschoolers, through song and animation.

4.title: Doctor
4.plot: Toodee gets sick and needs to rest. The doctor visits and everyone helps Toodee feel better.

5.title: Flying
5.plot: Brobee and friends go on a hot air balloon ride and meet new friend Sparkles.

6.title: Superhero
6.plot: Toodee rallies up the troops to play Superheroes. We meet Super Mr. Superhero who helps rescue a lost monster.

7.title: Circus
7.plot: The characters help Al the Ringmaster make a circus in Gabbaland! Brobee learns to be a clown, and everyone gets to perform.

8.title: Fairytale
8.plot: Lance reads a story to the characters where Jack (Muno) plants magic beans and climbs a beanstalk to meet the Giant (Brobee) and his bean machine.

9.title: Clubhouse
9.plot: Brobee and Muno build a boy's clubhouse but won't let Foofa and Toodee play. Lance and Plex help Foofa and Toodee build an awesome treehouse, and they let everyone play!

10.title: Treasure
10.plot: Two special guests travel to Gabbaland to search for hidden treasure with their compass. Everyone joins in the search and they do a special dance in the secret ice cave.

11.title: Pets
11.plot: Foofa gets a new pet called a Mokicho, but it becomes a lot of work. Plex explains the rules of pet care, and everyone helps Foofa care for the pets.

12.title: Baby
12.plot: Lance shows videos of when the Gabba friends were babies. Brobee helps feed Muno's baby brother, and we meet Plex's niece Plexee.

13.title: Bugs
13.plot: Muno takes us on a bug tour of Gabbaland! Plex shrinks the characters down to follow the Oskie bugs to their underground world where we meet the Queen Oskie Bug and watch eggs hatch.

16.title: Funtimes
16.plot: Mark Mouthersbaugh draws something and CBeebies presenters Andy, Rebecca, Cat, and Sid are featured in the Dancey Dance.

1.title: Beach
1.plot: DJ Lance and the Goobketeers play Cross it Out.

imdb.plot outline: Yo Gabba Gabba! is a fun live-action program for young children ages 1 and up. Join our host DJ Lance Rock as he introduces us to friendly toy monsters in a magical land full of music, dance, colorful cartoons and simple life lessons that will get you and your children up off the floor to learn and dance along. Muno, the red cyclops, Foofa the pink flower bubble, Brobee the green little one, Toodee the blue cat-dragon, and Plex the robot are ready to sing, play and teach whenever you're ready. Just say the magic words! YO GABBA GABBA!!
